nd, strand, metric, value, sample)` using\n`pivot_longer` on the `coverage*`/`numCs*` columns, and save it to\n`output/df_mku.rds`. Then pivot wide on `metric`, compute `mCpG = numCs / coverage`,\ngroup by `(sample, chr)`, and write the mean mCpG table to `output/mean_mcpg.tsv`\nusing `readr::write_tsv` with columns `sample, chr, mean_mCpG`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mean_mcpg.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_db\": {\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleA.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleA.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleA.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleA.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleB.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleB.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleB.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleB.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleC.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleC.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleC.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleC.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleD.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleD.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleD.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleD.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"mk_united.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_united.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_raXDtaw4WMnEheVUogGH2nzY", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R libraries: methylKit, dplyr, tidyr, and readr.\\n2. Read the methylKit object from the RDS file located at `input/mk_united.rds`.\\n3. Convert the methylKit object to a data frame and use `pivot_longer` to transform it into a long tibble format with columns `(chr, start, end, strand, metric, value, sample)`.\\n4. Save the long tibble to `output/df_mku.rds`.\\n5. Pivot the long tibble to a wide format on the `metric` column.\\n6. Calculate the mCpG value as the ratio of `numCs` to `coverage`.\\n7. Group the data by `sample` and `chr` and compute the mean mCpG for each group.\\n8. Write the resulting table to `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` using `readr::write_tsv`.\\n9. Verify the existence of `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (774 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_raXDtaw4WMnEheVUogGH2nzY"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_CUaXkc7VHLXajBLSBAoLawTR", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(readr)\\n\\n# Load the methylKit object\\nmethylBase <- readRDS(\\\"input/mk_united.rds\\\")\\n\\n# Convert to a data frame and pivot longer\\ndf_long <- methylBase %>%\\n  as.data.frame() %>%\\n  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with(\\\"coverage\\\") | starts_with(\\\"numCs\\\"),\\n               names_to = \\\"metric\\\",\\n               values_to = \\\"value\\\")\\n\\n# Save the long format tibble\\nsaveRDS(df_long, \\\"output/df_mku.rds\\\")\\n\\n# Pivot wider and calculate mCpG\\ndf_wide <- df_long %>%\\n  pivot_wider(names_from = metric, values_from = value) %>%\\n  mutate(mCpG = numCs / coverage)\\n\\n# Calculate mean mCpG per sample and chromosome\\nmean_mcpg <- df_wide %>%\\n  group_by(sample, chr) %>%\\n  summarize(mean_mCpG = mean(mCpG, na.rm = TRUE))\\n\\n# Write the result to a TSV file\\nwrite_tsv(mean_mcpg, \\\"output/mean_mcpg.tsv\\\")\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n    setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018BiocGenerics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    IQR, mad, sd, var, xtabs\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    anyDuplicated, aperm, append, as.data.frame, basename, cbind,\n    colnames, dirname, do.call, duplicated, eval, evalq, Filter, Find,\n    get, grep, grepl, is.unsorted, lapply, Map, mapply, match, mget,\n    order, paste, pmax, pmax.int, pmin, pmin.int, Position, rank,\n    rbind, Reduce, rownames, sapply, saveRDS, table, tapply, unique,\n    unsplit, which.max, which.min\n\nLoading required package: S4Vectors\n\nAttaching package: \u2018S4Vectors\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:utils\u2019:\n\n    findMatches\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    expand.grid, I, unname\n\nLoading required package: IRanges\nLoading required package: GenomeInfoDb\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:methylKit\u2019:\n\n    select\n\nThe followin